          nationality: "Macedonian",
          education: "Politecnico di Milano",
          specialism: "Architecture and engineering",
          bio: '<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">One of the things that I love about Powerhouse Company is the diversity, not only in the sense of a versatile portfolio and interdisciplinary design approach but also the international work environment. I like to be challenged and constantly improve; therefore, working from concept to construction and seeing a project through is a fantastic experience for me. As a Powerhousian, I get to do that with a fantastic team of people from different backgrounds and nationalities, allowing me to grow and learn both as a professional and an individual.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">The world is constantly changing, and things that used to be impossible are now part of our everyday lives. Especially with engineering, new possibilities are constantly being created, and it allows architecture to evolve along with it to new limits. This is very exciting to watch and be a part of as a professional. Given that our lives are morphing into something different with every new year, I enjoy the design challenges that come with it and figuring out how to make something work efficiently and reasonably. My dream projects would be of a social character and based on improving user experience. Projects that contribute to society and make a difference in people&#8217;s quality of life, like social housing, public spaces, schools, hospitals, etc. I believe that as architects, we have not only the possibility but also the responsibility to create a better environment for everyone.</span></p>\n',
