          bio: "<p>The best thing about my job, and the reason why I intend to become an architect, is the ability to connect people through design. The power of creating spaces to meet and get together, to work, to love, to live – that’s the unique gift of this profession. Architects can therefore be seen as mediators of society who build to connect and unite people of different ages, social backgrounds and nationalities under one roof.</p>\n<p>I’ve been a passionate football fan all my life. My childhood dream was to become a professional player, or a top manager. Despite being a huge football fan, I never had the chance to attend a top league match in a stadium until my 16th birthday when my father took me to the Allianz Arena to watch FC Bayern Munich play. To experience this special atmosphere and see all those people with completely different backgrounds united in pure passion and excitement under one roof – that was the turning point when I realized the power of architecture.  After that, I wanted to become an architect to bring people together. And who knows, maybe sometime in the future I might even be able to combine my passion for football and architecture – my dream project would be a football stadium to allow people to have the same powerful and vibrant experience that I enjoyed on my first visit.</p>\n",
