          bio: "<p>I first got to know Powerhouse Company five years ago. I was a site manager for a Munich-based company and Powerhouse was working on a family house in Munich. I noticed the high-quality, professional work they were doing there. Later, while I was working for a glass specialist in Munich, I worked with Sander Apperlo who had by then started Powerhouse’s Munich office – he need a good glass supplier for projects in St. Moritz and Rotterdam. It was a great collaboration, and Sander asked me if I want to join the new and growing office in Munich – an easy decision for me.  Above all, working for Powerhouse Company means working for a company that you identify with.</p>\n<p>The best thing about my job is that I need to get out to the construction site to see what’s going on – I don’t like to sit in the office every day in front of a computer. Managing all the different suppliers on site isn’t always easy, but I love working with other people, especially if they can teach me new things. Since we are working on international projects, I meet people from all over the world from different cultures and backgrounds, which is really interesting. Seeing all these different people working together to get a project done makes all the work (and sometimes trouble) worthwhile!</p>\n",
