            "The ambience of the office allows you to learn and work in the best possible way, surrounded by great people.",
          nationality: "Polish",
          education: "Silesian University of Technology in Gliwice, Poland",
          specialism: "Working on all stages",
          bio: "<p>Architecture holds a great responsibility in shaping and interacting with people&#8217;s lives through its functional and aesthetical aspects. Creating a<br />\nspace is a task with many layers and demands that has to be taken into the design process. It not only has a significant impact on our everyday life, but it can improve the quality of life in the long term through, for example, being environmentally conscious. I find it very inspiring how architecture combines many different fields altogether. If it&#8217;s either a hospital, library, or family house, the user&#8217;s needs are different. It requires a lot of<br />\nresearch and involves many people from different disciplines to create a functional space. Watching the projects evolve to<br />\nbecome physical spaces is very rewarding. If I didn&#8217;t choose architecture, I would still be working in a creative field like photography or filmmaking. It has a similar approach to how it communicates complex ideas and affects emotions through different mediums.<br />\nAs a Powerhousian, I get to work on unique projects that allow me to develop my skills and shape me as a designer. The office&#8217;s ambiance allows you to learn and work in the best possible way while being part of a very talented and experienced team. I get to learn<br />\nfrom and work with a very committed group of people with whom we also have a lot of fun.</p>\n",
