          quote: "",
          nationality: "Dutch",
          education: "Eindhoven University of Technology",
          specialism:
            "I'm experienced in the design of public buildings, cultural interventions and transformation of industrial sites.",
          bio: "<p>As an architect, I enjoy working with physical, social, or historical contexts. These are, for me, the tools for a fruitful and creative design process. I like working on transformation and public projects where I can tell a narrative—enhancing the values of an existing place, injecting something contemporary, and creating a story about the future. Or being challenged to create a space where people can gather and collectively experience a physical story.</p>\n<p>For me, the narrative continues with music. Whether I&#8217;m going to a concert or playing piano or guitar, music embodies my imagination.<br />\nI believe there is a connection between both creative processes. Playing with other musicians resembles the same collaboration I experience in an architectural design team. Everyone plays a different part, but together we&#8217;re composing a design.</p>\n",
