          quote:
            "As an architect, every design challenge represents a complex puzzle in which a large set of constraints can be turned into an advantageous opportunity.",
          nationality: "Dutch",
          education: "Eindhoven University of Technology ",
          specialism: "Architectural and Urban Design",
          bio: '<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">In the increasingly complex world we live in, the role of architecture is changing. With the enduring climate crisis, the question of what sustainable architecture looks like becomes increasingly relevant. Sustainability in buildings is not only concerned with the optimization of energy consumption and production. The most sustainable building is the product of a rational process, leading to high-quality architecture and vitality of the urban fabric. A building that has the capacity to remain relevant under changing urban dynamics will endure beyond its original function and take on more meaning over time. It is this consideration that brings the future of sustainability into the realm of urban architecture.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">As an architect, every design challenge represents a complex puzzle in which a large set of constraints can be turned into an advantageous opportunity. During my internship at Powerhouse Company, I witnessed the positive and inventive attitude among Powerhousians towards these so-called &#8216;design challenges&#8217;. The atmosphere in the office combines a strong passion for the buildings they create with having a good time while doing so! This motivated me to rejoin Powerhouse as a Junior Architect to continue shaping the built environment.</span></p>\n',
