          search: false,
          quote:
            "Integrating a complex and challenging program in one building and simultaneously making it look effortless and beautiful, is creating art.",
          nationality: "Dutch",
          education: "Windesheim University of Applied Sciences",
          specialism: "Architecture",
          bio: '<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">I was first introduced to Powerhouse Company when they gave a guest lecture on Merckt – a captivating and innovative building in Groningen. I found it fascinating to hear about the technical solutions to make the design possible. It is in the process from design to a building where you see the talent of an excellent structural engineer.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">What attracted me to Powerhouse Company the most was the architects&#8217; motivation and driven attitude. I always like to deliver the best work possible, and my colleagues have the same mentality. In addition, the Floating Office Rotterdam is the most amazing office you could wish for. It has an open ambiance, the view is impressive, and it is full of friendly people.</span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span style="font-weight: 400;">I have known that I wanted to become an architect for a few years now. This field allows me to combine my creative and technical sides. While buildings should be functional and suitable for the user, they can also be art forms. Since we live in a world surrounded by buildings, why not make them look good. </span></p>\n',
