          specialism:
            "I'm mainly involved in the project management and completion of our wonderful projects from a technical, scheduling, and cost point of view.",
          bio: "<p>The best thing about being an architect is that you get the opportunity to plan and influence the cityscape and the built environment, not just for a short period but for several decades. Even if we are no longer around, there will be buildings that we have worked on that our children and grandchildren will look at.</p>\n<p>As the environment changes more and more, we all want to build in a more environmentally friendly and climate-neutral manner. However, the regulations in several areas, such as fire protection and building physics, are becoming stricter. Therefore, it is a balancing act to build as climate-neutral as possible and at the same time comply with all regulations.</p>\n<p>I find inspiring in my field the extreme passion most architects share for their profession, which extends into their private lives. I know of few other disciplines that are as devoted to their work as architects. I look forward to realizing projects together with Powerhouse Company&#8217;s international and passionate family.</p>\n",
